column5: Greetings gang,  I'm kyle from Ancaster, been reading the forum for a bit - joined a while ago and figured id finally get around to introducing myself.  My grandparents have a cottage on lake Kasshabog up in 15 north of havelock....been fishing there for a number of years....I have an aluminum boat w/ a johnson and just recently bought a minnkota to use while portaging for my canoe.....i go on a couple trips per year, last year to the ottawa river and shining tree (where i will def'n be returning in september).....had some great days on the water.  Ive set my 09 goals to land a musky, and to have cosistent success on walleye on my home lake.  Im also a avid hunter, deer, turkey, grouse, - So far this year i harvested a 21lb tom on my 4th hunt of this season and pending success after work today or tomorrow i will be eating my second tag.  Cheers and good luck in the 09 season,
Welcome to the board K F, look forward to some posts and good luck on the musky this season.
Welcome aboard, Kyle...lookin' forward to some reports from the "other" 'Bog
welcome  Kash is a nice lake up there.   I have a friend in MacDonald Bay. You should have no problem getting your 1st muskie.
Welcome aboard Kyle. I too have a goal of landing a musky this year. 3 years of trying just ain't cutting it. Best of luck to ya and be sure to post of pic of her.
Welcome to OFC Kyle Looking forward to your future reports Leechman

Nice intro.  Loves to hunt and fish walleye and muskie... you'll do fine here!  Hope you don't have to eat tag soup on your 2nd turkey tag, like I did.  Turkey's are my favourite hunt of the year.  Good luck man, hope you get a long beard.
Looks like you'll fit right in here!  Welcome to the board...looking forward to seeing some of your reports this year.
